I added U-Force support to <a href="http://nintaco.com/" class="postlink">Nintaco</a> based on the technical information and controller mapping suggestions in <a href="http://problemkaputt.de/everynes.htm" class="postlink">Nocash's doc</a>.  The single prototype game that supports the U-Force analog features is not worth playing, but for those who want to try, I put some details <a href="http://nintaco.com/faq.html#U-Force" class="postlink">here</a>.  <br /><br />For those not fortunate enough to own the actual device, I recommend playing with those automatic paper towel dispensers, automatic faucets and automatic soap dispensers that you find a modern public bathroom.  They're based on the same technology and they're a lot more fun than this crappy peripheral.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6828">zeroone</a> — Sat Aug 11, 2018 3:26 pm</p><hr />
